2月7日上午，武汉市中心医院，市民自发献花悼念因感染新冠肺炎抢救无效逝世的医生李文亮，花束中有一张收据。
February 7 morning, Wuhan Central Hospital, the public spontaneously flowers to mourn the death of the new crown pneumonia doctor Li Wenliang, there is a receipt in the bouquet.
这里是李文亮生前工作过的院区。
This is the courtyard where Li Wenliang worked before his death.
2月7日凌晨3点48分，武汉中心医院官方微博宣布，该院眼科医生李文亮经全力抢救无效，于2月7日凌晨2点58分去世。
February 7, 3: 48 a.m., Wuhan Central Hospital, the official Weibo announced that the hospital's ophthalmologist Li Wenliang after full rescue failed, February 7 at 2: 58 a.m. died.
中青报·中青网记者 李峥苨/摄2月7日上午，武汉市中心医院，市民自发献花悼念昨晚因感染新冠肺炎抢救无效逝世的医生李文亮。
Chinese New Zealand newspaper Zhongqing Pneumonia reporter Li Zheng / February 7 morning, Wuhan city central hospital, citizens volunteered flowers to mourn the death of doctor Li Wenliang who died of pneumonia last night.
中青报·中青网记者 李峥苨/摄2月7日上午，武汉市中心医院后湖院区，市民在门诊楼前摆放花束和照片，悼念昨晚在这里因感染新冠肺炎抢救无效逝世的医生李文亮。
Chinese Youth Daily Li Zheng / She February 7 morning, Wuhan Central Hospital Houhu District, the public put flowers and photos in front of the outpatient building, to mourn the death of doctor Li Wenliang who died here last night from pneumonia.
花束中的卡片上写着：“疫情吹哨人，你是英雄，一路走好。
The card in the bouquet said, "The epidemic whistler, you are a hero, all the way.
”中青报·中青网记者 李峥苨/摄2月7日上午，武汉市中心医院后湖院区，市民在门诊楼前摆放花束和照片，悼念昨晚在这里因感染新冠肺炎抢救无效逝世的医生李文亮。
People put flowers and photos in front of the outpatient clinic building to mourn the death of doctor Li Wenliang who died of pneumonia last night.
中青报·中青网记者 李峥苨/摄2月7日上午，武汉市中心医院后湖院区，市民在门诊楼前摆放花束和照片，悼念昨晚在这里因感染新冠肺炎抢救无效逝世的医生李文亮。
Chinese Youth Daily Li Zheng / She February 7 morning, Wuhan Central Hospital Houhu District, the public put flowers and photos in front of the outpatient building, to mourn the death of doctor Li Wenliang who died here last night from pneumonia.
中青报·中青网记者 李峥苨/摄2月7日，北京通惠河边，积雪上写着“送别李文亮！”的文字。
The words "Farewell Li Wenliang!" were written on the edge of the Tonghui River in Beijing on February 7.
中青报·中青网记者 赵迪/摄2月7日，一位市民戴着口罩从北京通惠河边走过，对岸的积雪上写着“送别李文亮！”的文字。
ZHOU Di / She February 7, a citizen wearing a mask walked by the side of the Tonghui River in Beijing. On the other side of the bank, the words "Farewell Li Wenliang!" were written on the snow.
